# ─── Runtime / collector churn (local only) ───────────────────────────────────
# These are written continuously by running servers/collectors, so tracking them
# left the working tree permanently dirty and blocked branch-switch automation
# ("git_tree_dirty: refusing to switch branches"). Same policy as the other
# runtime data above (data/csf/, data/pcsf/, data/training/ …).
data/csf_cache/
data/*.out
apps/data/crypto/prices.jsonl
data/kalshi/paper-positions.jsonl
data/kalshi/cio-train-report.json
data/agent_hook_audit.jsonl

# ─── Runtime churn logs (#767/#777) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Append-only runtime logs/metrics, not curated data. They are rewritten on every
# chat / cube / csf op, so when tracked they chronically dirty the tree and the
# branch-switch guard refuses to switch ("git_tree_dirty … would be clobbered").
# Local-only; untracked via `git rm --cached` in the same commit that ignores them.
apps/data/csf-query-metrics.jsonl
data/convergence/chat-responses.jsonl
data/cubes/*/deltas/*.jsonl
data/proposals.jsonl
data/rag-intake/tesseract-trace/trace.jsonl

